Poids_naifs_M12

Cyrielle Codde

2026-01-07

Objective : to predict Weight_M12 meaning weight (kg) at time M12 using initial weight and other predictors as comedication, medical history, HIV history and socio demographic criterias only in naive patients.

Packages and file loading

library(tidyverse)
library(tidymodels)

DATAIDS_M12 <- read.csv("Poids_naifs_M12_19.07.23_CCodde.csv") %>%
  mutate(PATNUME2 =as.character(PATNUME2)) %>%
  mutate_if(is.character, factor) %>% 
  #French to English translate
  rename(Gender = SEXE, Age_visit = AGE_visite,
         Date_HIV = DATE_VIH, Age_diagnosis_HIV = AGE_DTIC_VIH,
         HIV1 = VIH1, HIV2 = VIH2,
         Year_visit = ANNEE_recours, Month_visit = MOIS_recours, Delta_HIV = Delta_VIH,
         Weight_M0 = Poids_T0, Weight_M12 = Poids_M12,
         AIDS_visit = SIDA_recours, HIV_load_log = CV_log, CD4CD8 = RatioCD4CD8,
         Birth_country = ZONE_GEO,
         # rename comorbidities
         HBV_coinfection = VHB, CHV_coinfection = VHC,
         Metabolic_disorders = Sd_metabo, Endocrine_risk_factors = FDR_endoc, Pregnancy = Grossesse,
         Delta_pregnancy = Delta_grossesse, Delta_menopause = Delta_meno,
         Sedentarity_mobility = Sedentarite_mobilite,Diet_habits = RHD,
         Thyrotoxicosis = Thyreotoxicose, Anorexia = Anorexie, Toxic_subts = Toxique,
         Mood_disorders = Tb_humeur, Schiz_disorders = Tb_schiz, Bulimia = Boulemie, Sleep_disorders = Sommeil,
         Non_compliance_ttt = Inobservance_Ttt, Enterocolitis = Enterocolites,
         # rename comedications
         Atypical_neuroleptics = Neuroleptiques_Atyp,Tricyclic_antidep = Antidep_Tricy,
         Others_antidep = Antidep_autres, Others_weight_loss = WL_autre,
         # rename ARV
         Line_ARV_regimen = Ligne_arv,Time_since_ARV_regimen = DUREE_ARV_visite,
         INSTI_G2 = INI_G2, INSTI = INI, NRTI = INTI, NNRTI = INNTI,PI = IP) %>%
  arrange(PATNUME2, Delta_HIV) %>% distinct()

Spliting for training and external validation

set.seed(1234)
dataids_split<- initial_split(DATAIDS_M12, strata = Weight_M12, prop=3/4)
dataids_train  <- training(dataids_split )
dataids_test  <- testing(dataids_split )

set.seed(123)
data_train_trains_set <- validation_split(dataids_train)
data_train_trains_set
## # Validation Set Split (0.75/0.25)  
## # A tibble: 1  2
##   splits              id        
##   <list>              <chr>     
## 1 <split [3212/1071]> validation
library(embed)
dataids_rec  <- recipe(Weight_M12 ~ ., data = dataids_train) %>%
  update_role(PATNUME2, new_role = "id") %>%
  #step_impute_knn(CV_log, CD4, RatioCD4CD8) %>% # Imput data with neighboring values
  # convert a nominal predictor into a single set of scores derived from a geenralized linear model
  step_lencode_glm(NUMCOREVIH, outcome = vars(Weight_M12)) %>%
  step_lencode_glm(Thymoreg_anticonv, outcome = vars(Weight_M12)) %>%
  step_lencode_glm(Tricyclic_antidep , outcome = vars(Weight_M12)) %>%
  step_lencode_glm(Others_antidep , outcome = vars(Weight_M12)) %>%
  step_lencode_glm(Cortico, outcome = vars(Weight_M12)) %>%
  #step_lencode_glm(GLP1,outcome = vars(Weight_M12)) %>%
  step_lencode_glm(Others_weight_loss, outcome = vars(Weight_M12)) %>%
  step_lencode_glm(Atypical_neuroleptics , outcome = vars(Weight_M12)) %>%
  step_nzv(all_factor_predictors()) %>%
#  step_zv(all_nominal_predictors()) %>% # Rm predictors with a single value
  step_dummy(Gender, Birth_country) # convert nominal data into numeric binary model terms

dataids_rec_prep <-  prep(dataids_rec )
dataids_train_recipe <-bake(dataids_rec_prep, new_data = NULL)
#dataids_test_recipe <-bake(dataids_rec_prep, new_data = dataids_test)

XGBoost (xgb)

xgb_spec <- boost_tree(mode = "regression",
                       mtry = tune(),
                       trees = 500,
                       min_n = tune(),
                       sample_size = tune(),
                       tree_depth = tune(),
                       stop_iter = tune(),
                       learn_rate = tune()) %>% set_engine("xgboost", validation = 0.2)

xgb_wf <- workflow() %>% add_recipe(dataids_rec) %>% add_model(xgb_spec)

# Finetune
set.seed(234)
tune_xgb_ft <- tune_grid(xgb_wf,data_train_trains_set,
                               grid = 60,
                               metrics = metric_set(rmse))

##Courbe Weight_M0 et Weight_M12
dataids_test %>% ggplot(aes(x=Weight_M12, y=Weight_M0)) + geom_point() + geom_smooth() + theme_bw()

ref_pred <- dataids_test %>%
  mutate(bias_rel = (Weight_M12 - Weight_M0)/Weight_M0,
         bias_rel_square = bias_rel * bias_rel)

rmse <- sqrt(mean((ref_pred$Weight_M12 - ref_pred$Weight_M0)^2))
var_y <- var(ref_pred$Weight_M0)

ref_pred_summary <- ref_pred %>%
  summarise(
    biais_rel = mean((Weight_M12 - Weight_M0) / Weight_M0),
    rmse = sqrt(mean((ref_pred$Weight_M12 - ref_pred$Weight_M0)^2)),
    relative_rmse = sqrt(mean(((Weight_M12 - Weight_M0) / Weight_M0)^2)),
    R2_rmse = 1 - (rmse^2 / var_y),
    biais_out_20per300 = mean(!between((Weight_M12 - Weight_M0) / Weight_M0, -0.2, 0.2)),
    nb_out_20per300 = sum(!between((Weight_M12 - Weight_M0) / Weight_M0, -0.2, 0.2)),
    n = n()
  )
rmarkdown::paged_table(as.data.frame(ref_pred_summary))

dataids_rec  <- recipe(Weight_M12 ~ ., data = dataids_train) %>%
  update_role(PATNUME2, new_role = "id") %>%
  #step_impute_knn(HIV_load_log, CD4, CD4CD8) %>% # Imput data with neighboring values
  # convert a nominal predictor into a single set of scores derived from a geenralized linear model
  step_lencode_glm(NUMCOREVIH, outcome = vars(Weight_M12)) %>%
  step_lencode_glm(Thymoreg_anticonv, outcome = vars(Weight_M12)) %>%
  step_lencode_glm(Tricyclic_antidep , outcome = vars(Weight_M12)) %>%
  step_lencode_glm(Others_antidep , outcome = vars(Weight_M12)) %>%
  step_lencode_glm(Cortico, outcome = vars(Weight_M12)) %>%
 # step_lencode_glm(GLP1,outcome = vars(Weight_M12)) %>%
  step_lencode_glm(Others_weight_loss, outcome = vars(Weight_M12)) %>%

library(glmnet)

## 1. Model specification
lasso_spec <- linear_reg(mode = "regression",
                         penalty = tune(),
                         mixture = 1) %>%
  set_engine("glmnet")

## 2. Workflow
lasso_wf <- workflow() %>%
  add_recipe(dataids_rec) %>%
  add_model(lasso_spec)

## 3. Tuning
set.seed(234)
tune_lasso <- tune_grid(lasso_wf,
                        resamples = data_train_trains_set,
                        grid = 10)

tune_lasso

Breakdown plot

https://github.com/pbiecek/breakDown & https://arxiv.org/abs/1804.01955 There are multiple possible approaches to understanding why a model predicts a given auc. One is a break-down explanation: it computes how contributions attributed to individual features change the mean models prediction for a particular observation.

set.seed(1234587)
zoom <- dataids_test %>% slice_sample(n=1)
bd_plot <- predict_parts(explainer = explainer_external,
                       new_observation = zoom,
                       type = "break_down")
plot(bd_plot, max_features = 5)
